From: Christian Kohn <chris.kohn@amd.com>
Subject: [PATCH] drm: Force legacy modesetting

Some DRM drivers (e.g. zynqmp-dpsub) advertise atomic modesetting
support but fail the test-only atomic commit, causing a segfault.

Force legacy modesetting mode as a workaround until the driver or
kmscon's atomic path is fixed.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [zynqmp-dpsub workaround]

AI-Generated: Claude Opus 4.6
Signed-off-by: Christian Kohn <chris.kohn@amd.com>
---
 src/uterm_drm_shared.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/src/uterm_drm_shared.c
+++ b/src/uterm_drm_shared.c
@@ -1022,6 +1022,9 @@
 		vdrm->legacy = true;
 	}

+	/* Force legacy modesetting to work around drivers that advertise
+	 * atomic support but fail the test-only atomic commit. */
+	vdrm->legacy = true;
 	ret = ev_eloop_new_fd(video->eloop, &vdrm->efd, vdrm->fd, EV_READABLE, io_event, video);
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_close;
